==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wait-a-bit
<hw>Wait"-a-bit`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Any of several plants bearing
thorns or stiff hooked appendages, which catch and tear the
clothing,</def> <specif>as:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
greenbrier.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any of various species of
hawthorn.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>In South Africa, one of numerous
acacias and mimosas.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>The grapple plant.</def>
<sd>(e)</sd> <def>The prickly ash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wait-a-while</ent>⟦br⟧
